5. Non-Functional Requirements and Design Decisions

Rather than discussing every non-functional requirement separately, this section focuses on the requirements that most strongly shaped the proposed REMS architecture. The most important concerns are auditability, confidentiality, usability, file versioning, and timely notifications. These concerns directly influenced why the system is divided into separate components such as the Authentication and Authorisation component,  Application Management Service, Validation Service, Document Management and Versioning Service, Notification Service, and Audit Trail Service.
